article.headline: Northeastern 73, Delaware 59
article.story: BOSTON -- Matt Janning scored 19 points and Manny Adako added 17 in Northeastern's 73-59 win over Delaware on Saturday. Chaisson Allen hit 12 points, nine rebounds and five assists as Northeastern (15-6, 10-1 Colonial Athletic Association) won its ninth game in 10 tries. Marc Egerson led Delaware (9-14, 3-8 CAA) with 26 points on 10-of-15 shooting and had a team-high eight rebounds. Alphonso Dawson scored 12 points for the Blue Hens. Up 39-31 with 15:40 to play, Northeastern scored 12 unanswered over the next three minutes. Northeastern closed out the first half on a 13-2 run, highlighted an acrobatic three-point play from Janning. Falling out of bounds, Janning floated the ball over the backboard and into the net as he was being fouled.
